The paper discusses a framework for assessing the quality of linked data, which involves data management (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.LG) techniques. It also involves software engineering (cs.SE) for the development of the framework and information retrieval (cs.IR) for querying the definitions.
